Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a pottery transport amphora, gradual curve. Clay near fine, micaceous, pink-red; cream slip. Circular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 206, 18 Common type.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1514)
